	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=64677"><span id="Sage">xaanru</span></a><br /><b><span id="Sage">Sage</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">3035 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>It is resistable damage. If the mob fails the resist check, the bow is a 31 damage bow for that melee round. For typical experience grind mobs, most of the resistable damage types (magic, poison, fire, cold, and disease) typically act just like (or real close to) an increase in the weapon base damage, however, against highly resistant mobs, these weapons become less effective. <br/><br/>So essentially, this bow is better than a 28/40 bow WITHOUT the poison damage, but it is LESS desirable than a straight 31 damage/40 delay bow, since 3 of the damage is resistable.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
